This was my first visit to Wing Stop. I placed my order. Ok cool. The cashier tells me that if I complete a survey, I'll get a free order of fries. Sounds good. I began to do the survey on their website as I waited for my order. I started encountering a series of questions that couldn't have the answer to yet (Did it take a long time to receive your order?). Nevertheless, I finished the survey. I showed the cashier that I completed it and when they called my name to claim my order, the same cashier looked in the bag and confirmed that the free fries were I there. Wonderful. I went home to find that I was given the wrong order. I wanted to fix what I was certain to be an honest (yet negligent) mistake, so I called the Wing Stop. As soon as the phone was answered, I heard someone rattle off about 2 unintelligible sentences that began with "thank you for calling Wing Stop". Before I can even speak, they just put the phone down as I could hear things going on in the store. They basically just answered the phone to stop it from ringing, with no intention of actually taking the call! 0 customer service skills on display here. I went back to the Wing Stop and I show the same cashier that my order is incorrect. They then tell me that I took someone else's food... even though they called my name. I had to laugh because the name of the person that order was intended for- their name sounds nothing like mine. Imagine standing in a Wing Stop, arguing with a cashier about whether your own name wasn't called. How silly that would have been. I just wanted the food I paid for. Instead of apologizing, they took my order out of the bag, put it on the counter then asked me if I want a bag... I replied yes, then they get another folded bag and hand me the bag to put my food in... even though the food was just in a bag. Imagine doubling down on a lie, then having an attitude about it... HORRIBLE. Very unpleasant with a "whatever" attitude. The food was alright, but would have been better if I got it 45 minutes earlier like I was supposed to. I don't think I'll go back to this Wing Stop, or maybe I'll have a better experience if that cashier moves on to another "whatever" job. If I could score this place 0 stars, I most definitely would.

I wanted to give this place three stars a few days ago. I decided to give it another try first. And now it gets 2 stars off the strength that the customer service is phenomenal.  The first time I went the "manager" was there. He was very attentive to the customers but was very overbearing ("Hi everyone, I am the manager and I'm sorry for the wait.....). I am not complaining about the wait time; apparently the wings are cooked to order. With the 18 to 25 min wait WINGSTOP could season the damn wings. Just because Ross is losing weight doesnt mean that we have to eat healthy too.  The sauces are excellent. Please throw some seasoning on the chicken.  If you're going here, order via their website ahead of time or you'll be sitting inside waiting for your food.  In their defense this is a new store. I hope they see this review.
